title: Next Generation of Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse Available
text: AUSTIN, Texas, March 17, 2021 /PRNewswire/ -- Today Oracle announced a set of innovative enhancements to Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse, the industry's first and only self-driving cloud data warehouse. With this latest release, Oracle goes beyond other cloud offerings by completely transforming cloud data warehousing from a complex ecosystem of products, tools, and tasks that requires extensive technical expertise, time and money to perform data loading, data transformation and cleansing, business modeling, and machine learning into an intuitive point-and-click, drag-and-drop experience for data analysts, citizen data scientists, and business users.

title: Oracle Cloud Gives Prosper Digital Therapeutics Tools to Boost Patient Care at Lower Cost
text: AUSTIN, Texas, March 18, 2021 /PRNewswire/ -- Oracle today announced that Prosper Digital Therapeutics (ProsperDTX), a company that pairs patient medical data with causal machine learning to develop personalized treatment plans, has selected Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) Data Science to host its machine learning platform. ProsperDTX uses Oracle Autonomous Data Warehouse and OCI Object Storage to ingest and store data from multiple sources, including medical records systems and wearables, in real-time for faster predictive modeling.

title: Oracle Cloud Extends Prosper Digital Therapeutics Tools To Facilitate Economical Patient Care

title: Oracle (ORCL) Cloud Leveraged by Prosper Digital Therapeutics

title: Oracle Prices $15 Billion Aggregate Principal Amount of Investment Grade Notes
text: AUSTIN, Texas, March 22, 2021 /PRNewswire/ -- Oracle Corporation (NYSE: ORCL) today announced the pricing of its sale of $2,750,000,000 of 1.650% Notes due 2026 (the "2026 Notes"), $2,000,000,000 of 2.300% Notes due 2028 (the "2028 Notes"), $3,250,000,000 of 2.875% Notes due 2031 (the "2031 Notes"), $2,250,000,000 of 3.650% Notes due 2041 (the "2041 Notes"), $3,250,000,000 of 3.950% Notes due 2051 (the "2051 Notes") and $1,500,000,000 of 4.100% Notes due 2061 (the "2061 Notes"). The offering is expected to settle on March 24, 2021, subject to customary closing conditions.

title: Oracle Raises $15B Via Medium, Long-Term Debt
text: Oracle Corp (NYSE: ORCL) priced the sale of $15 billion notes, including $2.75 billion of 1.650% notes due 2026, $2 billion of 2.300% notes due 2028, $3.25 billion of 2.875% notes due 2031, $2.25 billion of 3.650% notes due 2041, $3.25 billion of 3.950% notes due 2051 and $1.5 billion of 4.100% notes due 2061. The offering is expected to settle on March 24, 2021.

title: Oracle CEO Safra Cats netted more than $76 million through stock trades
text: Oracle Corp. Chief Executive Safra Catz netted more than $76 million through a number of stock trades, as she acquired 2.25 million shares through the conversion of derivatives then sold them in the open market at much higher prices. The enterprise software company disclosed in a Form 4 filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission late Monday that Catz acquired 1.10 million shares at $32.43 on March 19 and 1.15 million shares at $32.43 on March 22.

title: TIM Brasil Selects Oracle and Microsoft to Migrate All of its Datacenter Workloads to the Cloud
text: AUSTIN, Texas, March 24, 2021 /PRNewswire/ -- TIM Brasil, one of the largest telecommunications providers in Brazil with more than 61 million customers, today said that it has selected Oracle and Microsoft to migrate all of its on-premises workloads to the cloud. TIM Brasil is one of the first telecommunications companies in the country to move 100 percent of its workloads to the cloud.
